## What is this?

This is an **ADE (Agent Dev Environment)** — a Cursor workspace scaffolded from a [copier template](https://github.com/madi-parloa/ade-template). It contains:

- A portfolio of Parloa infrastructure repos listed in `ade-repos.txt` (cloned by copier `_tasks` during `copier copy` / `copier update`).
- GSD (Get Shit Done) installed workspace-locally for spec-driven development.
- The `claudes-kitchen/` and `open-kitchen/` repos cloned as reference source. Their setup scripts are NOT auto-run — they mutate user/system state (see `claudes-kitchen/setup-cooking-environment.sh`). Run them manually if you want global installation.
- Pre-seeded codebase intelligence in `.planning/codebase/` so GSD is immediately Parloa-aware.

## Quick start

This ADE was created with:

```bash
uvx copier copy --trust git+https://github.com/madi-parloa/ade-template.git <this-directory>
```

## Re-syncing and updating

One command pulls latest template changes, clones any new repos, pulls latest on existing ones, and re-installs GSD (idempotent):

```bash
uvx copier update --trust
```

If you just want to re-sync repos after editing `ade-repos.txt` (without pulling template changes), `copier update` still does the right thing — it's the single supported entry point for both flows.

## Producing a different ADE

1. **Different repos** — re-run copier with `--data portfolio_file=/path/to/my-repos.txt`, or edit `ade-repos.txt` and run `uvx copier update --trust`.
2. **Fork the template** — `gh repo fork madi-parloa/ade-template --remote` and scaffold from your fork.

## Files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `AGENTS.md` | Agent-level workspace context (what repos are here, conventions, guardrails) |
| `CLAUDE.md` | Claude-specific instructions |
| `ade-repos.txt` | Git URLs of repos to clone |
| `.planning/PROJECT.md` | GSD project definition |
| `.planning/codebase/*.md` | Pre-seeded codebase intelligence |
| `.cursor/` | Workspace-local Cursor config (populated by copier `_tasks` / GSD) |
